      • getExitCode

        @Nullable
public java.lang.String getExitCode(int requestCode,
                                              int resultCode,
                                              @Nullable
                                              android.content.Intent data)

        Returns the exit code from the Streem experience if requestCode represents an Activity that was started by the Streem SDK. Otherwise returns null. This method should be called from Activity.onActivityResult or Fragment.onActivityResult.

        For a tutorial, this will be the exit code specified in the tutorial's step destination. This can also be EXIT_CODE_HELP or EXIT_CODE_EXIT if the user exited via one of the toolbar buttons.

        See Also:
        requestCode, Activity.onActivityResult, Fragment.onActivityResult

      • initialize

        @JvmStatic
 @NotNull
public static Streem initialize(@NotNull
                                                     android.app.Application application,
                                                     @NotNull
                                                     java.lang.CharSequence appId,
                                                     @NotNull
                                                     android.support.v4.util.Consumer<java.lang.Throwable> errorListener)

        Initializes the Streem SDK. Should be called in the Application's onCreate method.

        Parameters:
        appId - application's ID provided by Streem.
        errorListener - callback that will be called if an error is encountered by theStreem SDK (at any point in the future, not only during initialization). The callbackwill be called on the Android main thread.
